# Frontend Rules

## TypeScript
- Keep strict typing.
- Prefer generated API types.
- Avoid `any`; justify if unavoidable.
- Use adapters only when transforming API data for UI.

## React
- Keep components small and explicit.
- Server state belongs in TanStack Query.
- Local UI state stays local.
- Avoid global state unless shared across distant screens.
- Do not duplicate backend permissions; use backend hints for display only.

## API
- API calls live outside components.
- Use shared API client/retry/error helpers.
- Mutations must invalidate precise query keys.
- Optimistic UI needs rollback/error behavior.

## UI
- Loading, empty, error, unauthorized, and offline states must be explicit.
- Icon-only buttons need accessible names.
- Do not break route/back behavior.
- Do not reintroduce legacy shell/nav into terrain routes.

## Tests
Add/update tests for routing, query behavior, mutations, permissions, forms, empty/error/loading states.
Run relevant: `npm run typecheck`, `npm run lint`, `npm test`, `npm run build`.